  "prompt": "Halloween walk in York?",
  "response": "York, with its rich history and reputed haunted spots, is an ideal place for a Halloween walk. Here are a few popular options you might consider:\n\n1. **The York Ghost Walk Experience**: This is one of the most famous ghost walks in York. It takes you through the city's most haunted locations with intriguing stories from York's dark history.\n\n2. **The Original Ghost Walk of York**: Established in 1973, this is the first ghost walk in the world. This tour will guide you through some of York's most historic and haunted sites.\n\n3. **Ghost Hunt of York**: This is a more interactive experience, where you can actively seek out paranormal activity with the help of a knowledgeable guide.\n\n4. **Treasurer's House**: Famous for the sighting of Roman soldiers, Treasurer's House is a hot spot for ghost stories.\n\n5. **The Shambles**: This narrow, medieval street is not only picturesque but also reputedly haunted.\n\n6. **York Dungeon**: Though not a walk, the Dungeon offers a frightening insight into York\u2019s history with actors and special effects.\n\nBefore heading out, it's worth checking for any special Halloween events or additional tours, as many places offer exclusive experiences around this time. Make sure to dress warmly, as it can get quite chilly in late October.",
